title: Keuhkot
text:
Keuhkot (English: Lungs) is a Finnish one man avantgarde band, whose only member is Kake Puhuu (aka Kalevi Rainio) from Pomarkku. Keuhkot started in 1988. Keuhkot's music has been described as post-punk, industrial or antimusic. Keuhkot concerts are performances in which Kake Puhuu may perform from large bird nest boxes or from lecterns.
